We can estimate the weight of the resistor by multiplying its power by its resistance. Assuming that the resistor has a resistance value of 10Ω (which is the midpoint of its specified range), we get:
Weight = 7W * 10Ω = 70 g
Therefore, the weight of the 7W Micron power resistor of the MVR series is 70 grams.
